ce:section.ce:para:
To investigate the optical properties of CDs/PVA films, we examined the morphology, UV absorption, and fluorescence emission of CDs/PVA. The optical photographs of the four CDs films with varied CDs content (1–5 wt%) in daylight were shown in Fig. 5

                        a (when the CDs content was above 5 wt%, the films showed more darkness and its transparency decreased). The CDs are homogeneously distributed in PVA, although the color of the CDs films gradually deepens with the content of CDs increasing. When the films with different CDs contents were placed on the paper printed with “XATU”, it hardly affected the legibility of the lettering (
                           Fig. S2
                        ), indicating that the CDs films still maintained a high degree of transparency. We conducted structural analysis on PVA and CDs/PVA using XRD and XPS, and the data results showed that CDs were successfully doped into PVA films (
                           Figs. S3-S5

                        ).
